---- MODULE TLAPS ----
EXTENDS Integers, Sequences
==============================
Temporal logic for actions.  This version of temporal logic only handles enabled formulas and ignores time bounds (i.e., it assumes that all action occurrences are instantaneous).   The following rules were obtained from the paper "The Temporal Logic of Actions" by Jensen, Mellish, and Schaeffer:
* WF2(M) = ∃ g . EM <<M>>_g (WF1(M))    [definition]
* SF2(M) = ∀ g . ENABLED <<M>>_g → EF <<M⟩_g   [definition]
* TLA4: M \in WF2 <=> M \notin SF2     [temporal logic rule STL4, special case for enabled formulas and instantaneous action occurrences only; note that the general temporal logic proof rules from "The Temporal Logic of Actions" cannot yet be handled by TLAPS]
* WF1(M) = ∀ g . M \in <<M>>_g     [definition, special case for enabled formulas and instantaneous action occurrences only; note that the general temporal logic proof rules from "The Temporal Logic of Actions" cannot yet be handled by TLAPS]
* EF(M) = ∀ g . M \notin <<M>>_g     [definition, special case for enabled formulas and instantaneous action occurrences only; note that the general temporal logic proof rules from "The Temporal Logic of Actions" cannot yet be handled by TLAPS]
* WF2(EM) = ∃ g . EM <<M>>_g (WF1(EM))     [definition, special case for enabled formulas and instantaneous action occurrences only; note that the general temporal logic proof rules from "The Temporal Logic of Actions" cannot yet be handled by TLAPS]
* SF2(EM) = ∀ g . ENABLED <<M>>_g → EF <<M⟩_g     [definition, special case for enabled formulas and instantaneous action occurrences only; note that the general temporal logic proof rules from "The Temporal Logic of Actions" cannot yet be handled by TLAPS]
* WF1(EM) = ∀ g . EM \in <<M>>_g     [definition, special case for enabled formulas and instantaneous action occurrences only; note that the general temporal logic proof rules from "The Temporal Logic of Actions" cannot yet be handled by TLAPS]
* EF(EM) = ∀ g . EM \notin <<M>>_g     [definition, special case for enabled formulas and instantaneous action occurrences only; note that the general temporal logic proof rules from "The Temporal Logic of Actions" cannot yet be handled by TLAPS]
* WF2(EM) = ∃ g . EM <<M>>_g (WF1(EM))     [definition, special case for enabled formulas and instantaneous action occurrences only; note that the general temporal logic proof rules from "The Temporal Logic of Actions" cannot yet be handled by TLAPS]
* SF2(EM) = ∀ g . ENABLED <<M>>_g → EF <<M⟩_g     [definition, special case for enabled formulas and instantaneous action occurrences only; note that the general temporal logic proof rules from "The Temporal Logic of Actions" cannot yet be handled by TLAPS]
* WF1(EM) = ∀ g . EM \in <<M>>_g     [definition, special case for enabled formulas and instantaneous action occurrences only; note that the general temporal logic proof rules from "The Temporal Logic of Actions" cannot yet be handled by TLAPS]
* EF(EM) = ∀ g . EM \notin <<M>>_g     [definition, special case for enabled formulas and instantaneous action occurrences only; note that the general temporal logic proof rules from "The Temporal Logic of Actions" cannot yet be handled by TLAPS]
